-## 17. Dashboard and API security
+## 17. Evidence-driven self-learning
+
+1. Outcome attribution uses only verified Paper or authenticated Testnet evidence. Synthetic,
+   demo, fixture and mock outcomes are excluded from reputation and challenger evidence.
+2. Every attribution is immutable, idempotent, finite and SHA-256 protected. Attributed PnL
+   and drawdown contributions must reconcile exactly to the settled outcome.
+3. Challenger creation requires minimum sample, multiple market regimes, calibration,
+   profitability and integrity gates. Missing evidence cannot be interpreted as zero.
+4. Automatic promotion is permitted only to **Paper research champion**. It may change the
+   research policy used by future Paper experiments, but it cannot alter an experiment
+   promotion stage, campaign, scaling authority, deployment, credentials, capital or flags.
+5. Automatic execution promotion is forbidden. Testnet, controlled scaling and every future
+   Mainnet transition remain separate evidence-gated manual decisions.
+6. A challenger that fails drawdown, calibration, integrity, sample or improvement gates is
+   retained as blocked evidence and cannot become research champion.
+7. The self-learning supervisor is observable, bounded and restart-safe. Its failure degrades
+   learning only; it cannot reopen a closed position, submit an order or bypass reconciliation.
+8. Dashboard learning views are read-only except for an authenticated research-cycle trigger.
+   They use safe DOM APIs, cancellation, backoff, mobile layout and truthful unavailable state.
